# Engineering Principles

## Product Boundaries
- Build for a real user problem, not just a demo
- Prefer small usable features over large speculative ones
- Define acceptance before implementation

## Technical Rules
- Prefer simple solutions
- Avoid unnecessary abstraction
- Reuse existing modules before adding new ones
- Keep diffs small, commit often

## Testing Standard
- Every bug fix gets a regression test
- Every feature gets at least one happy-path test
- Critical logic should be covered before refactoring

## Definition of Done
- spec updated
- tasks checked off
- tests passing
- README or related docs updated
